name: Rocky 689
text:
Friendly people here. To get in the gate you have to enter your po# as the pin on the touchscreen
box. Took me a minute to figure that out, and then the gate will open. No one answers that call box or the phone number they have on there for assistance. My appointment was for btwn 3:30 - 5:30. Got here at 4:00, They called me for a door at 5 and I was finished for 7:30. Not sure if they allow dogs but i let mines out to potty. No one came running outside to tell me no..lol..also i parked to sleep and no one said anything. Couple of other drivers parked so i figured it was ok. Not a big lot to turn when a lot of trucks are here during the day, but you can still turn around, its just a bit tight. Docks are not too hard to get into unless you get the end dock, that one might be a lil difficult. Other then that not a bad place to load.
